- Cremation.
- We can't just do that ourselves.

252
00:19:47,236 --> 00:19:49,569
No. State law.
It has to be someone licensed.

253
00:19:50,364 --> 00:19:51,946
We don't have to have him embalmed,

254
00:19:52,783 --> 00:19:55,150
but the body does have
to be handled.

255
00:19:56,412 --> 00:19:57,744
In three weeks he'll be...

256
00:19:57,830 --> 00:19:59,287
Yes. He'll be melted.

257
00:20:02,042 --> 00:20:03,042
Unless...

258
00:20:07,256 --> 00:20:08,337
In your basement.

259
00:20:10,718 --> 00:20:12,129
You can't be serious.

260
00:20:13,262 --> 00:20:15,254
How badly do you want this, Jess?

261
00:20:22,646 --> 00:20:23,853
[water trickling]

262
00:20:48,672 --> 00:20:50,254
Oh, God.

263
00:20:54,136 --> 00:20:57,675
Jess, give me a hand. You gotta
give me a hand here, Jess.

264
00:20:58,724 --> 00:21:00,181
Try to free the arm.

265
00:21:00,267 --> 00:21:02,224
Get the arm off
the banister there.

266
00:21:05,689 --> 00:21:08,056
Jesse, for God's sake,
I'm losing him!

267
00:21:17,618 --> 00:21:19,450
- [doorbell rings]
- [Jessica whimpers]

268
00:21:20,662 --> 00:21:22,198
[grunting]

269
00:21:25,292 --> 00:21:26,453
It's the nurse.

270
00:21:28,962 --> 00:21:30,498
- Answer it.
- No.

271
00:21:30,589 --> 00:21:33,193
If you don't answer it, she'll be
bugging us all night. Get rid of her.

272
00:21:33,217 --> 00:21:34,503
[doorbell ringing]

273
00:21:43,435 --> 00:21:44,596
[doorbell rings]

274
00:21:45,687 --> 00:21:50,523
Uh, I... I should have called you.
I'm sorry. Uh, I won't be needing you.

275
00:21:51,193 --> 00:21:53,526
[sighs] I came all this way.

276
00:21:53,612 --> 00:21:55,812
- I'm gonna have to charge you for my time.
- [thumping]

277
00:21:57,950 --> 00:21:59,407
Will you be wanting me tomorrow?

278
00:22:00,285 --> 00:22:02,151
No. Uh...

279
00:22:02,955 --> 00:22:05,868
Actually, I have decided
to take your advice.

280
00:22:05,958 --> 00:22:08,792
I-I'm... I'm putting Mr. Valdemar
into a hospital.

281
00:22:09,378 --> 00:22:12,371
- I won't be needing you anymore.
- Well, it is about time.

282
00:22:12,464 --> 00:22:14,171
A man in his advanced state.

283
00:22:14,842 --> 00:22:17,505
I'm here. I would be happy
to look in on him.

284
00:22:17,594 --> 00:22:20,257
[Jessica] Uh, no. Uh, the doctor's
with him right now.

285
00:22:20,347 --> 00:22:22,930
Well, I'm sorry to lose the work,

286
00:22:23,016 --> 00:22:26,384
but I am glad to see that you are
finally doing the right thing.

287
00:22:26,854 --> 00:22:28,971
I'll see that they send you
an adjusted bill.

288
00:22:29,064 --> 00:22:30,396
- Good night.
- Good night.

289
00:22:30,482 --> 00:22:32,724
Thank you... for all your help.

290
00:22:35,529 --> 00:22:36,940
[exhales deeply]

291
00:22:50,794 --> 00:22:52,786
[crickets chirping]

292
00:22:59,636 --> 00:23:01,502
What if we need more signatures?

293
00:23:03,682 --> 00:23:06,925
[Robert] I've done enough.
You can do the forging.

294
00:23:11,148 --> 00:23:13,140
You better practice,
just in case.

295
00:23:15,068 --> 00:23:18,061
What if Pike calls,
wants to talk to him?

296
00:23:18,780 --> 00:23:21,067
No phone calls.
Doctor's orders.

297
00:23:22,367 --> 00:23:24,950
- What if he comes to the house?
- He won't.

298
00:23:25,037 --> 00:23:27,765
He gives you a hard time, but underneath
it all, he doesn't give a shit.

299
00:23:27,789 --> 00:23:30,372
As long as he gets his fees,
that's all he cares about.

300
00:23:31,001 --> 00:23:33,288
That's all anybody
ever cares about in the end.

301
00:23:35,130 --> 00:23:37,372
- Money.
