You're not gonna freak out on me,
are you?

324
00:26:35,185 --> 00:26:37,097
You're gonna be able
to get through this.

325
00:26:37,187 --> 00:26:39,179
Because if you're not,
tell me now,

326
00:26:39,856 --> 00:26:42,269
so I can pull out
and start covering my tracks.

327
00:26:42,359 --> 00:26:46,319
He said, in his typically kind
and understanding way.

328
00:26:47,030 --> 00:26:50,489
I am sorry, Robert,
if I am not strong enough for you.

329
00:26:50,575 --> 00:26:54,114
I didn't go to medical school. I haven't
spent a lot of time around cadavers.

330
00:27:20,272 --> 00:27:23,686
[metronome ticking]

331
00:27:25,610 --> 00:27:26,896
What are you doing?

332
00:27:27,696 --> 00:27:29,813
