You should do the same.

333
00:27:30,657 --> 00:27:32,176
I can give you something, if you like.

334
00:27:32,200 --> 00:27:34,783
God, no. After all that gin, you'd drop.

335
00:27:36,079 --> 00:27:39,618
I should teach you how to do this.
Self-hypnosis. It's better than any pill.

336
00:27:40,834 --> 00:27:42,270
You know, you won't be able
to wake me.

337
00:27:42,294 --> 00:27:46,163
So if you think you might change your mind
and want to mess around...

338
00:27:46,256 --> 00:27:48,748
- I won't be able to wake you?
- When you're hypnotized,

339
00:27:48,842 --> 00:27:51,334
you can only be wakened
by the voice that put you under.

340
00:27:52,095 --> 00:27:54,031
When you hypnotize yourself,
there's no such voice.

341
00:27:54,055 --> 00:27:56,968
- I need to have you with me.
- I am with you.

342
00:27:57,058 --> 00:27:59,095
[scoffs] If I can't wake you...

343
00:27:59,186 --> 00:28:01,269
I have got to get some sleep.

344
00:28:01,771 --> 00:28:05,060
I have an early appointment.
I've been neglecting my practice.

345
00:28:05,150 --> 00:28:07,142
You're not the only one
that's strung out, Jess.

346
00:28:07,235 --> 00:28:10,603
The last few weeks haven't exactly
been a vacation for me either.

347
00:28:11,823 --> 00:28:14,907
I'm here. I'm with you.
Nothing is gonna happen.

348
00:28:14,993 --> 00:28:17,030
[ticking continues]

349
00:28:17,120 --> 00:28:18,907
I'm just gonna sleep
for a few hours.

350
00:28:46,066 --> 00:28:47,182
Robert.

351
00:28:47,275 --> 00:28:50,734
[ticking continues]

352
00:28:50,820 --> 00:28:51,901
Robert.

353
00:28:54,950 --> 00:28:55,986
Bastard.

354
00:28:57,619 --> 00:28:59,611
[ticking]

355
00:29:17,806 --> 00:29:22,801
- [moaning]
- [dog howling]

356
00:29:23,895 --> 00:29:25,011
Robert.

357
00:29:27,482 --> 00:29:28,848
Goddamn you.

358
00:29:28,942 --> 00:29:31,605
[ticking continues]

359
00:29:31,695 --> 00:29:33,937
[water trickling]

360
00:30:10,942 --> 00:30:12,808
[trickling continues]

361
00:30:18,283 --> 00:30:20,275
- [clattering]
- [gasps]

362
00:30:25,707 --> 00:30:27,573
[sighs]

363
00:30:37,010 --> 00:30:39,002
[trickling continues]

364
00:30:50,648 --> 00:30:53,436
[moaning]

365
00:30:53,526 --> 00:30:54,892
[gasps]

366
00:30:56,446 --> 00:30:58,358
Robert. Robert.

367
00:30:58,448 --> 00:31:01,612
Wake up! Robert, wake up!
Robert!

368
00:31:01,701 --> 00:31:03,988
[moaning]

369
00:31:04,079 --> 00:31:06,071
[metronome ticking]

370
00:31:13,004 --> 00:31:15,496
[birds twittering]

371
00:31:18,176 --> 00:31:20,919
[metronome ticking]

372
00:31:29,062 --> 00:31:30,553
He's still alive.

373
00:31:35,860 --> 00:31:39,228
Here. Here. Take a look at him.
See for yourself.

374
00:31:40,657 --> 00:31:42,614
Come down here,
Jessica, and look at him.

375
00:31:42,700 --> 00:31:46,239
Just take one look at him,
then tell me you think he's still alive.

376
00:31:46,329 --> 00:31:47,365
I can't.

377
00:31:47,455 --> 00:31:50,118
[water trickling]

378
00:31:50,208 --> 00:31:54,202
[moaning]

379
00:32:00,969 --> 00:32:02,505
Uh, Valdemar?

380
00:32:06,099 --> 00:32:07,465
Are you there?

381
00:32:08,643 --> 00:32:11,056
[Ernest] Yes.

382
00:32:18,945 --> 00:32:23,531
Valdemar, uh,
are you still, uh...

383
00:32:23,616 --> 00:32:25,699
[Ernest] Sleeping.

384
00:32:27,370 --> 00:32:28,486
Sleeping?

385
00:32:28,997 --> 00:32:30,579
[Ernest] Yes.

386
00:32:31,458 --> 00:32:33,370
No.

387
00:32:33,460 --> 00:32:36,999
I have been sleeping,

388
00:32:37,964 --> 00:32:39,580
and now...

389
00:32:40,425 --> 00:32:43,589
I am dead.

390
00:32:43,678 --> 00:32:46,216
Oh, Mother of God.

391
00:32:50,935 --> 00:32:52,096
[Robert] Valdemar.

392
00:32:59,611 --> 00:33:00,727
Valdemar.

393
00:33:04,657 --> 00:33:06,239
Valdemar, can you hear me?

394
00:33:15,001 --> 00:33:16,993
[footsteps approaching]

395
00:33:18,671 --> 00:33:21,539
Nothing. Over an hour,
and nothing more.

396
00:33:22,509 --> 00:33:26,253
It's a trick.
It... It's a recorded voice.

397
00:33:27,138 --> 00:33:29,676
- Someone's doing this to us. Pike.
- Oh, please.

398
00:33:29,766 --> 00:33:32,679
- It's either that, or he's still alive.
- He's dead, Jessica.

399
00:33:32,769 --> 00:33:35,682
There's no vital signs.
He's frozen solid, for Christ's sake.

400
00:33:37,398 --> 00:33:40,562
I don't know. I mean,
I don't know what's going on here.

401
00:33:41,152 --> 00:33:44,987
All I can think is that he was
hypnotized when he died, so...

402
00:33:45,073 --> 00:33:48,237
somehow we're still able
to communicate with him.

403
00:33:50,328 --> 00:33:51,785
It seems impossible, but...

404
00:33:52,747 --> 00:33:55,239
there's no other explanation
that makes any sense.

405
00:34:02,090 --> 00:34:03,581
Here. Here.

406
00:34:03,675 --> 00:34:06,167
Take two of these now,
and take another at 11:00.

407
00:34:06,261 --> 00:34:07,627
And lay off the liquor.

408
00:34:10,389 --> 00:34:12,130
- You're not leaving.
- I have to.

409
00:34:12,225 --> 00:34:13,806
Robert, you can't.

410
00:34:13,893 --> 00:34:16,260
I have an endoscopy at 8:00.

411
00:34:16,353 --> 00:34:19,250
They're prepping the patient right now.
I've canceled this guy three times.

412
00:34:19,274 --> 00:34:20,560
You can't do this to me.

413
00:34:22,735 --> 00:34:24,772
We are felons, Jessica.

414
00:34:24,862 --> 00:34:26,853
We have committed
grand larceny here

415
00:34:26,947 --> 00:34:30,112
and fraud and God knows what else.

416
00:34:30,201 --> 00:34:32,784
The last thing we need to do
is to arouse suspicion.

417
00:34:32,870 --> 00:34:35,533
We have to maintain
an air of, uh...

418
00:34:36,040 --> 00:34:37,531
An air of normality?

419
00:34:40,837 --> 00:34:43,123
[sighs] Look.

420
00:34:43,214 --> 00:34:45,877
Uh, I'll leave early.
I'll be back here by 2:30.

421
00:34:45,967 --> 00:34:49,380
You don't have to stay in the house.
Go outside. Get some air.

422
00:34:49,469 --> 00:34:51,928
Take the pills,
and calm yourself.

423
00:34:53,474 --> 00:34:55,010
Take the pills, Jessica.

424
00:35:03,484 --> 00:35:05,066
No booze, Jessica.

425
00:35:09,240 --> 00:35:10,240
Here.

426
00:35:14,579 --> 00:35:15,865
Let me see you take 'em.

427
00:35:26,257 --> 00:35:27,589
I'm terrified.

428
00:35:30,803 --> 00:35:32,339
I know...

429
00:35:33,222 --> 00:35:34,429
I'm sorry.

430
00:35:35,933 --> 00:35:37,469
I shouldn't be so, uh...

431
00:35:43,983 --> 00:35:45,224
We'll be all right.

432
00:35:45,693 --> 00:35:48,151
Just try to think logically.

433
00:35:49,030 --> 00:35:51,443
There's a logical explanation
for everything.

434
00:35:54,869 --> 00:35:57,486
There's a logical explanation
for everything.

