452
00:37:18,703 --> 00:37:20,569
Very bright.

453
00:37:21,247 --> 00:37:22,863
Very far...

454
00:37:23,708 --> 00:37:25,540
in the distance.

455
00:37:26,210 --> 00:37:28,702
Can't reach them.

456
00:37:29,380 --> 00:37:32,873
Where I am, it is dark.

457
00:37:34,218 --> 00:37:37,177
Dark. Cold.

458
00:37:38,765 --> 00:37:41,599
Very cold.

459
00:37:43,144 --> 00:37:46,637
Help me, Jessica!

460
00:37:46,731 --> 00:37:48,017
God.

461
00:37:48,733 --> 00:37:51,851
- Jesse?
- No. No...

462
00:37:51,944 --> 00:37:54,607
Christ. Don't go
spooking around like that.

463
00:37:54,697 --> 00:37:57,030
[Ernest] Others.

464
00:38:01,454 --> 00:38:03,992
There are others.

465
00:38:06,626 --> 00:38:08,788
- Others?
- [Ernest] Many...

466
00:38:09,295 --> 00:38:12,003
many others.

467
00:38:12,965 --> 00:38:14,922
Looking at me.

468
00:38:15,718 --> 00:38:17,425
Watching me.

469
00:38:18,554 --> 00:38:21,262
They want something.

470
00:38:23,142 --> 00:38:24,849
These, uh, others...

471
00:38:25,394 --> 00:38:26,805
can you see them?

472
00:38:27,396 --> 00:38:30,935
What do they look like?
Who are they?

473
00:38:33,236 --> 00:38:34,272
Valdemar.

474
00:38:36,739 --> 00:38:37,855
Valdemar.

475
00:38:41,410 --> 00:38:42,526
[button clicks]

476
00:39:02,682 --> 00:39:06,392
