Valdemar, I'm here.

495
00:40:28,184 --> 00:40:29,300
I'm with you.

496
00:40:30,227 --> 00:40:32,219
[Ernest] Help me.

497
00:40:33,940 --> 00:40:35,647
What... What can I do?

498
00:40:36,442 --> 00:40:39,105
[Ernest] Wake me.

499
00:40:39,779 --> 00:40:43,272
- Wake you?
- [Ernest] I am dead.

500
00:40:44,742 --> 00:40:46,608
Let me go.

501
00:40:47,912 --> 00:40:51,576
Wake me and let me go.

502
00:40:55,002 --> 00:40:56,994
[birds twittering]

503
00:41:10,059 --> 00:41:11,971
Wake you? Of course.

504
00:41:13,729 --> 00:41:17,222
You're still... You're still hypnotized.
If I wake you...

505
00:41:17,316 --> 00:41:20,184
[Ernest] I will be released.

506
00:41:20,987 --> 00:41:24,480
Quickly. The others.

507
00:41:24,573 --> 00:41:27,111
The others are coming.

508
00:41:28,160 --> 00:41:31,574
I am part of both worlds.

509
00:41:32,373 --> 00:41:35,582
Theirs and yours.

510
00:41:35,668 --> 00:41:38,035
They want to use me

511
00:41:38,129 --> 00:41:40,086
to pass through.

512
00:41:40,172 --> 00:41:44,587
To pass through.
They're coming.

513
00:41:44,677 --> 00:41:48,091
Wake me.
Wake me before...

514
00:41:54,729 --> 00:41:55,729
It's over.

515
00:41:59,358 --> 00:42:00,358
It's finished.

516
00:42:08,325 --> 00:42:09,816
[Robert] How could you do this?

517
00:42:10,369 --> 00:42:12,326
How in the hell
could you do this?

518
00:42:14,248 --> 00:42:16,285
What are we supposed
to do now, Jessica?

519
00:42:16,667 --> 00:42:18,750
How do we explain
two bullet holes in his body

520
00:42:18,836 --> 00:42:21,453
when he is supposed
to have died of natural causes?

521
00:42:21,547 --> 00:42:23,960
We don't have to explain anything.
We're gonna bury him.

522
00:42:25,968 --> 00:42:28,255
- Bury him.
- In the woods, out back.

523
00:42:28,345 --> 00:42:29,345
Oh...

524
00:42:29,430 --> 00:42:32,093
We'll say we took him
somewhere else for the funeral.

525
00:42:32,600 --> 00:42:34,842
- His hometown. Harrisburg.
- Oh, Christ.

526
00:42:34,935 --> 00:42:37,723
We have money, Robert.
It's just like you said.

527
00:42:38,355 --> 00:42:40,517
People won't ask
too many questions.

528
00:42:40,608 --> 00:42:43,396
They'll cooperate,
as long as there's enough money.

529
00:42:43,486 --> 00:42:46,229
I'm a living example of that.
God, I never should have...

530
00:42:46,322 --> 00:42:49,611
We have to bury him, Robert.
It's the only way to be rid of this.

531
00:42:54,038 --> 00:42:55,574
He asked me to...

532
00:42:56,916 --> 00:43:00,409
let him go, to wake him.

533
00:43:00,503 --> 00:43:04,122
He was not dead.
He couldn't have been dead.

534
00:43:04,757 --> 00:43:05,918
It's not possible.

535
00:43:06,675 --> 00:43:10,544
Somehow the hypnosis
kept him alive.

536
00:43:10,638 --> 00:43:12,254
What if he's still...

537
00:43:13,933 --> 00:43:14,933
How can we bury him

538
00:43:15,017 --> 00:43:18,010
- if there's still a chance that he might...
- We have no choice, Robert.

539
00:43:18,646 --> 00:43:20,262
We have no choice.

540
00:43:23,818 --> 00:43:25,150
You have no choice.

541
00:43:27,029 --> 00:43:29,149
If they find out about me,
they'll find out about you.

542
00:43:29,240 --> 00:43:30,731
I'll deny it.

543
00:43:30,825 --> 00:43:33,158
[stammers]
I'll deny everything.

544
00:43:34,829 --> 00:43:36,491
Deny you talked to Pike?

545
00:43:36,580 --> 00:43:38,287
[thunderclap]

546
00:43:42,878 --> 00:43:44,961
[thunder rumbling]

547
00:43:45,047 --> 00:43:47,039
[shovel scraping]

548
00:43:56,600 --> 00:43:59,559
[dog barking in distance]

549
00:44:11,657 --> 00:44:14,775
[thunderclaps]

550
00:44:17,413 --> 00:44:19,905
[chorus vocalizing]

551
00:44:41,979 --> 00:44:44,392
- Robert?
- [thunderclap]

552
00:44:58,120 --> 00:45:00,203
[thunderclaps continue]

553
00:45:06,879 --> 00:45:09,212
- Robert?
- [thunderclap]

554
00:45:16,764 --> 00:45:18,255
Robert, is that you?

555
00:45:19,350 --> 00:45:24,812
[Ernest] They're coming for you,
Jessica.

556
00:45:25,564 --> 00:45:28,398
They're coming for you.

557
00:45:30,444 --> 00:45:32,902
They don't want me...

558
00:45:32,988 --> 00:45:37,574
to go into the ground.

559
00:45:37,660 --> 00:45:38,660
Oh!

560
00:45:49,838 --> 00:45:52,205
[thunder rumbling]

561
00:46:05,854 --> 00:46:08,767
It isn't me, Jessica.

562
00:46:09,441 --> 00:46:12,184
It's the others.

563
00:46:13,112 --> 00:46:14,648
[gunshot]

564
00:46:18,033 --> 00:46:21,777
It's the others, Jessica.

565
00:46:22,746 --> 00:46:25,614
Using my body.

566
00:46:25,708 --> 00:46:27,449
[gunshot]

567
00:46:29,545 --> 00:46:32,583
I asked you to help me.

568
00:46:33,465 --> 00:46:36,458
You should have helped me.

569
00:46:37,678 --> 00:46:41,547
Now it's too late!

570
00:46:42,391 --> 00:46:45,850
[laughing]

571
00:46:58,907 --> 00:47:00,193
[gunshot]

572
00:47:00,826 --> 00:47:02,192
[moans]

573
00:47:03,996 --> 00:47:07,285
[laughing]

574
00:47:12,629 --> 00:47:14,370
[screams]

575
00:47:16,216 --> 00:47:17,832
[screams]

576
00:47:19,345 --> 00:47:20,711
[gunshot]

577
00:47:22,598 --> 00:47:24,464
[thunder rumbles]

578
00:47:44,828 --> 00:47:47,445
[Ernest laughing]

579
00:47:51,668 --> 00:47:54,752
[laughing continues]

580
00:47:58,675 --> 00:47:59,836
Valdemar.

581
00:48:00,386 --> 00:48:02,548
- I'm gonna wake you, Valdemar!
- [laughing]

582
00:48:02,638 --> 00:48:04,049
I'm gonna count to five.

583
00:48:05,432 --> 00:48:07,890
One! Two!

584
00:48:09,061 --> 00:48:11,804
- Three! Four!
- [laughing]

585
00:48:11,897 --> 00:48:13,729
Five!

586
00:48:13,816 --> 00:48:15,557
[laughing stops]

587
00:48:20,155 --> 00:48:21,817
[Ernest] It's too late.

588
00:48:23,409 --> 00:48:27,744
The others... [laughing]

589
00:48:27,830 --> 00:48:29,492
The others.

590
00:48:31,125 --> 00:48:34,664
Without me, they can't return.

591
00:48:34,753 --> 00:48:37,416
[laughing]

592
00:48:41,427 --> 00:48:44,591
They're with you now.

593
00:48:45,597 --> 00:48:48,340
They're with you.

594
00:49:18,255 --> 00:49:20,542
[wheels squeaking]

595
00:49:36,690 --> 00:49:38,773
- [thunder continues]
- [door opens]

596
00:49:38,859 --> 00:49:40,100
[door closes]

597
00:49:41,987 --> 00:49:44,900
[man] Come on. Let's go. Nice night...

598
00:49:46,575 --> 00:49:49,818
- Watch that umbrella.
- [man 2] Come on. We got one over here.

599
00:49:51,371 --> 00:49:53,863
[man] All right.
Let 'em through here. Let 'em through.

600
00:49:59,421 --> 00:50:01,083
[man 2] That's good right there.

601
00:50:04,468 --> 00:50:05,754
Come on.

602
00:50:15,354 --> 00:50:17,207
[detective] Guess she was
gonna bury him back here.

603
00:50:17,231 --> 00:50:19,439
She couldn't have dug
that grave by herself.

604
00:50:22,152 --> 00:50:24,485
We figure she popped him,
then shot herself.

605
00:50:25,489 --> 00:50:27,151
Very strange things though.

606
00:50:28,116 --> 00:50:30,073
We found blood in the freezer
down in the cellar.

607
00:50:30,160 --> 00:50:31,492
Christ.

608
00:50:32,996 --> 00:50:34,203
Rich people.

609
00:50:34,915 --> 00:50:37,453
The sick stuff always turns out
to be rich people.

610
00:50:39,127 --> 00:50:42,165
- She had him in the freezer, huh?
- [detective] That's what we think.

611
00:50:43,048 --> 00:50:45,415
- [thunder rumbles]
- [shutter clicks]

612
00:50:45,509 --> 00:50:47,421
And there was blood
in the freezer.

613
00:50:48,428 --> 00:50:50,385
So she had him down there
after he was shot.

614
00:50:50,472 --> 00:50:53,260
- Looks that way.
- So how'd he get up here?

615
00:50:53,850 --> 00:50:55,261
That's what we're asking ourselves.

616
00:50:56,186 --> 00:50:59,099
Wait. Wait till you get
a load of this.

617
00:51:04,361 --> 00:51:05,897
Oh, my God.

618
00:51:07,155 --> 00:51:09,147
This guy's been dead for weeks.

619
00:51:09,241 --> 00:51:11,198
[thunder rumbling]

620
00:51:11,285 --> 00:51:13,777
[metronome ticking]

621
00:51:18,834 --> 00:51:20,291
[ticking continues]

622
00:51:31,221 --> 00:51:34,214
[wind howling]

623
00:51:40,397 --> 00:51:43,606
[distorted voices, faint]

624
00:51:52,117 --> 00:51:54,404
[thunder continues]

625
00:52:03,503 --> 00:52:05,335
[ticking continues]

626
00:52:19,853 --> 00:52:21,845
[ticking continues]

627
00:52:34,951 --> 00:52:36,533
[tires screech]

628
00:52:41,833 --> 00:52:43,950
- Hey, 9-1-1?
- Yeah.

629
00:52:44,044 --> 00:52:48,209
It's god-awful. Screaming, crying,
like somebody's in some real pain.

630
00:52:49,007 --> 00:52:52,796
- How long's this been going on?
- A week. Two weeks maybe.

631
00:52:52,886 --> 00:52:55,754
Long enough to have the rest of us
in the building crazy over it.

632
00:52:56,223 --> 00:52:59,432
Couldn't get anyone to do anything
about it. You know how people are.

633
00:52:59,518 --> 00:53:01,475
Shit. It's driving me to drink.

634
00:53:01,937 --> 00:53:05,146
- I'm the guy who called 9-1-1.
- Well, you did the right thing.

635
00:53:10,278 --> 00:53:11,860
Police, Hoffman! Open up!

636
00:53:16,076 --> 00:53:17,783
[moaning]

637
00:53:18,704 --> 00:53:19,704
Hit it.

638
00:53:28,964 --> 00:53:30,080
Hoffman?

639
00:54:10,297 --> 00:54:13,961
What'd I tell you? Another rich guy.
Call in the troops.

640
00:54:15,135 --> 00:54:16,467
[uncocks gun]

641
00:54:37,783 --> 00:54:40,571
- [Robert moaning]
- [mouthing words]

642
00:54:41,536 --> 00:54:42,652
[Robert] Help.

643
00:54:43,371 --> 00:54:46,159
There's no one to wake me.

644
00:54:47,584 --> 00:54:49,951
No one to wake me.

645
00:54:50,045 --> 00:54:51,081
What?

646
00:54:52,297 --> 00:54:55,131
Oh! Oh!

647
00:54:56,635 --> 00:54:59,252
- [gunshots]
- No!

648
00:55:00,847 --> 00:55:04,181
- Oh!
- [metronome ticking]

649
00:55:13,527 --> 00:55:16,190
[man narrating] <i>It's the depravity
that's in all of us.</i>

650
00:55:20,659 --> 00:55:24,278
<i>Perversity is one of
the prime impulses of the heart.</i>

651
00:55:24,830 --> 00:55:26,162
<i>Who's never done
something wrong</i>

652
00:55:26,248 --> 00:55:29,207
<i>- just because it was forbidden?</i>
- [man] Watch your step there.

653
00:55:29,292 --> 00:55:31,909
[narrator] <i>To be evil only
for the love of being evil.</i>

654
00:55:34,256 --> 00:55:37,169
Sir, do you think there's
any chance of me being transferred

655
00:55:37,259 --> 00:55:39,467
back to parking violations?

656
00:55:39,970 --> 00:55:42,963
- No. I... I don't want any dinner, O'Neill.
- [gags]

657
00:55:43,056 --> 00:55:44,843
Maybe just some coffee.

658
00:55:44,933 --> 00:55:47,892
[O'Neill]
No, sir. I was asking about a transfer.

659
00:55:47,978 --> 00:55:52,018
- Out. Oh, I'm real impressed. Out.
- [man] This is a pass to come in here.

660
00:55:52,107 --> 00:55:53,835
- Can you read English?
- [man 2] I can read English.

661
00:55:53,859 --> 00:55:56,087
I can read any language you want.
You don't come in with one of those.

662
00:55:56,111 --> 00:55:58,068
I want the police!
I want to see the police!

663
00:55:58,154 --> 00:56:00,758
[detective] What's the matter, Rod? You
having a little problem with the bouncer?

664
00:56:00,782 --> 00:56:02,301
- He's all right.
- There's the police.

665
00:56:02,325 --> 00:56:03,325
Be my guest.

666
00:56:08,623 --> 00:56:11,491
How is it you get sent down
on every one of these, huh?

667
00:56:12,085 --> 00:56:13,792
Still life is my specialty.

668
00:56:16,172 --> 00:56:17,379
- [beeping]
- Already get him?

669
00:56:17,841 --> 00:56:21,175
Yeah, this morning.
Bastard was asleep, right next to her.

670
00:56:21,261 --> 00:56:23,298
[camera shutter clicking rapidly]

671
00:56:23,889 --> 00:56:26,256
- So who was the first one on the scene?
- Valenz.

672
00:56:37,193 --> 00:56:39,401
[chattering]

673
00:56:42,824 --> 00:56:44,190
[shutter clicks]

674
00:56:47,329 --> 00:56:48,329
[man] Man! Oh!

675
00:56:49,456 --> 00:56:51,823
Hey, Usher. Who the hell
told you to pull that lever?

676
00:56:53,793 --> 00:56:56,536
You trying to get somebody killed?
Somebody stop this thing.

677
00:56:56,630 --> 00:56:58,997
- I'm sorry.
- [detective] You're sorry.

678
00:57:00,842 --> 00:57:02,834
[shutter clicking rapidly]

679
00:57:03,595 --> 00:57:05,086
Look at him taking pictures,
will ya?

680
00:57:05,180 --> 00:57:06,967
[chuckles]

681
00:57:07,057 --> 00:57:10,016
What's the big hurry, Usher?
Stiff's not going anywhere.

682
00:57:10,101 --> 00:57:11,433
[chuckles]

683
00:57:38,046 --> 00:57:39,253
[meows]

684
00:57:42,634 --> 00:57:46,048
- [purring]
- Where did you come from?

685
00:57:46,137 --> 00:57:48,049
[purring]

686
00:57:48,765 --> 00:57:50,927
- [meows]
- How did you get in here?

687
00:57:53,353 --> 00:57:55,686
Oh. You have to get off the paper.
Come on.

688
00:57:55,772 --> 00:57:58,731
[purring]

689
00:57:58,817 --> 00:58:01,309
How did you get in here?
How did you...

690
00:58:01,403 --> 00:58:03,019
[screeches]

691
00:58:04,990 --> 00:58:07,218
- What did you do to her?
- [Usher] What did I do to her?

692
00:58:07,242 --> 00:58:08,449
Look what she did to me.

693
00:58:08,535 --> 00:58:10,868
- [meows]
- Whose cat is it?

694
00:58:10,954 --> 00:58:14,197
- [meows]
- Did you scratch him?

695
00:58:14,833 --> 00:58:17,041
You mustn't do that.
He's very fragile.

696
00:58:17,127 --> 00:58:19,961
- Where did she come from?
- She's ours.

697
00:58:20,755 --> 00:58:22,246
I found her outside.

698
00:58:23,008 --> 00:58:26,422
You were so hungry, weren't you?
But I'll take care of you.

699
00:58:27,512 --> 00:58:28,878
Isn't she pretty?

700
00:58:28,972 --> 00:58:30,658
She has a beautiful white spot
on her chest.

701
00:58:30,682 --> 00:58:31,889
[purring]

702
00:58:33,643 --> 00:58:34,683
We can keep her, can't we?

703
00:58:38,565 --> 00:58:39,726
Sure, honey.

704
00:58:40,233 --> 00:58:41,233
Good.

705
00:58:59,586 --> 00:59:03,796
[chanting in foreign language]

706
00:59:21,566 --> 00:59:23,558
[chanting continues]

707
00:59:25,820 --> 00:59:27,812
- [sighs]
- [chanting stops]

708
00:59:40,418 --> 00:59:42,330
- [woman] What is it?
- [Usher] The cat.

709
00:59:42,420 --> 00:59:45,413
- I think it's staring at me.
- [woman] My brave lover.

710
00:59:46,007 --> 00:59:48,819
Yeah, well, what if it decides to jump up
here in the middle of the night

711
00:59:48,843 --> 00:59:51,130
and claw my eyes out?

712
01:00:08,279 --> 01:00:09,861
[cat meowing]

713
01:00:13,618 --> 01:00:14,904
Better? Hmm?

714
01:00:15,620 --> 01:00:16,861
[snaps fingers]

715
01:00:30,969 --> 01:00:32,961
I can be brave when I have to.

716
01:00:34,973 --> 01:00:38,637
I see a lot of terrible things
in my work. You don't know.

717
01:00:40,019 --> 01:00:41,601
You're superstitious.

718
01:00:43,481 --> 01:00:45,188
I think it's 'cause she's
a black cat.

719
01:00:48,486 --> 01:00:51,729
You know where those superstitions began,
don't you? It was in the Middle Ages.

720
01:00:53,825 --> 01:00:57,614
Inquisitors burned women and black cats
'cause they thought they were witches.

721
01:00:57,704 --> 01:01:00,071
Finally, there weren't
many black cats left.

722
01:01:01,958 --> 01:01:04,450
Cats remember,
so they don't trust.

723
01:01:07,088 --> 01:01:09,922
[wind chimes clinking]

724
01:01:19,350 --> 01:01:21,888
[clinking continues]

725
01:01:29,903 --> 01:01:32,566
- [scratching]
- [meowing]

726
01:01:39,245 --> 01:01:41,282
[low growl]

727
01:01:47,754 --> 01:01:49,837
- [screeching]
- [gasps]

728
01:02:08,483 --> 01:02:11,317
[violins: classical]

729
01:02:13,655 --> 01:02:15,655
[woman] No, that's "B" natural.
- [music continues]

730
01:02:15,740 --> 01:02:16,740
- Good.
- [music stops]

731
01:02:16,824 --> 01:02:18,360
Try the whole thing
from the beginning.

732
01:02:19,577 --> 01:02:21,409
Three, four.

733
01:02:21,496 --> 01:02:24,580
[music resumes]

734
01:02:39,389 --> 01:02:42,132
[music continues]

735
01:02:57,573 --> 01:02:58,984
[music stops]

736
01:03:05,206 --> 01:03:07,166
- [imitates camera shutter clicking]
- [low growl]

737
01:03:10,586 --> 01:03:13,420
[music resumes]

738
01:03:19,846 --> 01:03:21,257
[low growl]

739
01:03:33,192 --> 01:03:34,728
[low growl]

740
01:03:35,361 --> 01:03:37,193
[screeches]

741
01:03:53,838 --> 01:03:55,079
[cat screeches]

742
01:04:02,138 --> 01:04:03,174
[screeches]

743
01:04:14,025 --> 01:04:15,937
What happened?
I heard her screaming.

744
01:04:16,027 --> 01:04:18,644
I accidentally caught her tail
in the door.

745
01:04:18,738 --> 01:04:20,946
She's all right.
By the way, what's her name?

746
01:04:21,949 --> 01:04:22,985
It's a secret.

747
01:04:24,202 --> 01:04:26,194
[laughs]

748
01:04:32,043 --> 01:04:33,079
Don't hurt her.

749
01:04:35,671 --> 01:04:38,334
[descending stairs]

750
01:04:43,554 --> 01:04:45,386
[man] News International,
