coming down the stairs.

1011
01:31:07,345 --> 01:31:10,804
I didn't... didn't realize it.
Oh. Oh.

1012
01:31:11,224 --> 01:31:13,716
- I better take care of it. Good night.
- Yeah.

1013
01:31:14,268 --> 01:31:17,056
And, uh, don't forget
about the music. I mean...

1014
01:31:17,146 --> 01:31:18,432
- [Usher] Yes.
- Okay.

1015
01:31:21,693 --> 01:31:22,693
[music ends]

1016
01:31:23,987 --> 01:31:26,104
[Usher]
<i>"Life here has become ugly.</i>

1017
01:31:26,656 --> 01:31:27,772
<i>I'm leaving you.</i>

1018
01:31:28,825 --> 01:31:32,159
<i>I know enough of what has happened
to never want to see you again.</i>

1019
01:31:33,287 --> 01:31:35,028
<i>Do not look for me."</i>

1020
01:31:49,303 --> 01:31:52,717
<i>You wanted to leave me,
but now we're together forever.</i>

1021
01:32:13,286 --> 01:32:14,286
[doorbell rings]

1022
01:32:16,247 --> 01:32:18,159
Hi. I'm here for my lesson.

1023
01:32:18,249 --> 01:32:20,332
Not today.
We're leaving.

1024
01:32:21,210 --> 01:32:23,998
Leaving? But Annabel told me
I had a lesson...

1025
01:32:24,088 --> 01:32:27,126
She must have made a mistake.
We're going on a vacation.

1026
01:32:27,216 --> 01:32:28,752
- Well, can...
- 954? Mr. Usher?

1027
01:32:28,843 --> 01:32:31,551
- Come on in.
- Well, can I at least say good-bye?

1028
01:32:31,637 --> 01:32:34,095
She's sleeping. Just put it right there.

1029
01:32:34,182 --> 01:32:36,299
Make sure to be quiet.
Somebody's sleeping.

1030
01:32:37,727 --> 01:32:39,309
Quiet. Somebody's sleeping.

1031
01:32:44,650 --> 01:32:46,562
[horn honks]

1032
01:33:19,811 --> 01:33:21,723
[watch beeping]

1033
01:33:25,399 --> 01:33:28,813
Sorry about last night. Annabel and me...

1034
01:33:28,903 --> 01:33:33,238
Oh, for me? Oh, how sweet.

1035
01:33:34,200 --> 01:33:37,944
You know how it is.
We had an argument. Pfft.

1036
01:33:38,037 --> 01:33:40,620
- Oh, nothing serious, I hope.
- No.

1037
01:33:41,707 --> 01:33:44,144
As a matter of fact, we're going away
for a week to be alone together.

1038
01:33:44,168 --> 01:33:49,129
Oh, that'll be so nice. Annabel needs it.
She's been kind of gloomy

1039
01:33:49,215 --> 01:33:51,693
- ever since her cat disappeared.
- So we'll see you next week.

1040
01:33:51,717 --> 01:33:53,049
Say good-bye to Mr. Pym for me.

1041
01:33:53,136 --> 01:33:55,970
Oh, he'll be right back.
You can catch him before we go out.

1042
01:33:56,848 --> 01:33:57,848
You're going out?

1043
01:33:58,474 --> 01:34:01,137
My hubby's taking me
to the movies tonight.

1044
01:34:01,227 --> 01:34:02,843
We love the movies.

1045
01:35:12,340 --> 01:35:13,626
[horn honks]

1046
01:35:14,342 --> 01:35:15,503
[Usher] Mr. Pym.

1047
01:35:15,593 --> 01:35:17,321
- Mrs. Pym. See you next week.
- [Mrs. Pym] Oh, look.

1048
01:35:17,345 --> 01:35:19,962
- [groans] Ah!
- [laughs]

1049
01:35:21,933 --> 01:35:25,472
- The bastard!
- Come on. He's just trying to be friendly.

1050
01:35:25,561 --> 01:35:27,974
Imagine taking a vacation
in this weather.

1051
01:35:30,691 --> 01:35:33,775
[Usher] <i>They saw us leaving together.
Two witnesses.</i>

1052
01:35:34,403 --> 01:35:36,736
Nobody will think of looking
for you in the house.

1053
01:35:48,751 --> 01:35:51,710
[seagulls cawing]

1054
01:35:59,679 --> 01:36:03,673
Mister. Your drink.

1055
01:36:04,517 --> 01:36:05,758
Thanks.

1056
01:36:06,686 --> 01:36:09,770
- How's your wife feeling?
- Much better, thanks.

1057
01:36:10,523 --> 01:36:11,934
In fact, she's leaving today.

1058
01:36:12,024 --> 01:36:14,687
Nothing worse than getting sick
on your vacation, huh?

1059
01:36:14,777 --> 01:36:16,609
- Will you be eating here?
- Yes.

1060
01:36:17,113 --> 01:36:18,979
After I drop her off
at the station.

1061
01:36:36,007 --> 01:36:38,215
[phone rings]

1062
01:36:40,469 --> 01:36:42,961
[phone rings]

1063
01:36:52,648 --> 01:36:55,106
[phone rings]

1064
01:36:56,110 --> 01:36:59,148
- Hello.
- [dial tone humming]

1065
01:37:12,543 --> 01:37:15,001
[phone rings]

1066
01:37:19,467 --> 01:37:20,503
Hello.

1067
01:37:23,262 --> 01:37:26,255
- Hello!
- [dial tone humming]

1068
01:37:31,270 --> 01:37:32,556
[soft banging]

1069
01:38:40,172 --> 01:38:42,539
Hey, sorry. It's just me.
It's Christian.

1070
01:38:42,633 --> 01:38:45,842
- [Usher] What are you doing here?
- I left my violin.

1071
01:38:45,928 --> 01:38:48,341
I've been calling all week,
but nobody answered.

1072
01:38:48,431 --> 01:38:51,031
- And I need to practice, so I...
- Well, you got it. Now get out.

1073
01:38:51,100 --> 01:38:55,094
- All right. Where's Annabel?
- She's left.

1074
01:38:56,689 --> 01:38:58,125
She's gone on tour with
an orchestra.

1075
01:38:58,149 --> 01:39:00,516
She'll be gone for a while.
Two, three weeks.

1076
01:39:00,609 --> 01:39:02,521
- You have her address?
- No.

1077
01:39:02,611 --> 01:39:05,479
[phone rings]

1078
01:39:05,573 --> 01:39:07,610
She... She's traveling a lot.

1079
01:39:07,700 --> 01:39:09,987
[phone rings]

1080
01:39:10,077 --> 01:39:12,694
- Hello.
- [man] <i>Hi. Can I speak to Annabel?</i>

1081
01:39:12,788 --> 01:39:14,654
- Hmm?
<i>- She gave me this number.</i>

1082
01:39:14,748 --> 01:39:15,909
<i>Is she there?</i>

1083
01:39:17,168 --> 01:39:18,409
No, she's left.

1084
01:39:18,502 --> 01:39:22,792
<i>- I don't understand.</i>
- Who... Who is this? Did you call before?

1085
01:39:23,549 --> 01:39:25,791
- What do you want?
<i>- What do you mean, she's left?</i>

1086
01:39:26,260 --> 01:39:29,879
<i>I've been waiting for her in New York
for a week. I don't mean to pry, but...</i>

1087
01:39:29,972 --> 01:39:31,972
[shouting] What do you mean
you're waiting for her?

1088
01:39:32,808 --> 01:39:34,640
Who are you, her boyfriend or something?

1089
01:39:36,103 --> 01:39:38,595
Listen, asshole. You better listen to me.

1090
01:39:38,689 --> 01:39:42,603
Don't you ever
call this house again. Ever!

1091
01:39:42,943 --> 01:39:43,979
You hear me?

1092
01:39:46,363 --> 01:39:48,980
- That's strange.
- What?

1093
01:39:49,074 --> 01:39:52,074
Well, you think if she'd have gone
on tour, she would have taken her violin.

1094
01:39:54,830 --> 01:39:56,162
She has two.

1095
01:39:57,416 --> 01:39:59,936
Look, I heard what you were saying
to that guy on the telephone.

1096
01:40:00,586 --> 01:40:02,293
- I mean, if...
- What do you want?

1097
01:40:02,379 --> 01:40:04,939
You don't know anything,
so why don't you mind your own business.

1098
01:40:08,344 --> 01:40:09,835
And don't come back.

1099
01:40:12,515 --> 01:40:14,757
Oh, Mr. Usher.

1100
01:40:14,850 --> 01:40:16,432
- You're back.
- Just me.

1101
01:40:16,519 --> 01:40:18,226
Yeah, Annabel went on tour,

1102
01:40:18,312 --> 01:40:20,975
only she didn't take her violin
and she never got there.

1103
01:40:21,941 --> 01:40:25,059
Well, uh,
will she be away long?

1104
01:40:25,152 --> 01:40:28,236
Two or three months.
If they want her longer, who knows.

1105
01:40:28,322 --> 01:40:30,484
Don't listen to this guy.
He's a damned liar.

1106
01:40:31,200 --> 01:40:35,114
Well, I'll miss her. Your wife
and I love to talk together.

1107
01:40:35,204 --> 01:40:37,821
- You mean Annabel?
- Yes.

1108
01:40:38,832 --> 01:40:43,122
- She's not my wife.
- Oh? I-I thought...

1109
01:40:43,212 --> 01:40:45,532
We've lived together for four years,
but we're not married.

1110
01:40:46,090 --> 01:40:47,090
Oh.

1111
01:40:47,174 --> 01:40:50,918
Well, uh, come on, Gloria.
Excuse us.

1112
01:40:51,011 --> 01:40:52,218
Don't worry about it.

1113
01:40:55,516 --> 01:40:56,882
And you, stay away.

1114
01:40:57,977 --> 01:40:59,218
You're lying, man.

1115
01:41:04,650 --> 01:41:05,686
You're lying!

1116
01:41:07,611 --> 01:41:08,611
He's lying!

1117
01:41:10,489 --> 01:41:11,855
He knows where she is.

1118
01:41:27,631 --> 01:41:30,419
[object rattling]

1119
01:41:34,847 --> 01:41:37,840
[rattling continues]

1120
01:41:49,028 --> 01:41:50,940
[phone rings]

1121
01:41:53,991 --> 01:41:56,404
[scratching]

1122
01:41:59,288 --> 01:42:01,029
[scratching continues]

1123
01:42:05,461 --> 01:42:07,794
[phone rings]

1124
01:42:15,346 --> 01:42:17,303
I told you not to call back.

1125
01:42:26,690 --> 01:42:28,852
[scratching continues]

1126
01:42:51,507 --> 01:42:54,341
[scratching continues louder]

1127
01:43:06,271 --> 01:43:08,711
[Usher] <i>Must have gotten inside
while I was building the wall.</i>

1128
01:43:10,567 --> 01:43:11,774
[screeches]

1129
01:43:17,116 --> 01:43:19,699
[screeching continues]

1130
01:43:27,668 --> 01:43:29,910
[loud screeching]

1131
01:43:49,857 --> 01:43:52,395
Mr. Usher. Hi.

1132
01:43:53,277 --> 01:43:54,984
My name's Father Hammer.
I'm your neighbor.

1133
01:43:55,070 --> 01:43:56,070
Hello.

1134
01:43:58,157 --> 01:44:00,740
- It's leaking.
- Yeah, it's blood.

1135
01:44:00,826 --> 01:44:02,783
- [Hammer] Oh.
- [Usher] It's a rat.

1136
01:44:03,620 --> 01:44:06,454
- A big rat.
- Where did it come from?

1137
01:44:07,541 --> 01:44:09,703
It got into my house,
and I had to kill it.

1138
01:44:10,502 --> 01:44:14,371
Huge. I stabbed it a few times,
but, uh, it wouldn't die.

1139
01:44:14,465 --> 01:44:16,206
So I had to keep on stabbing it.

1140
01:44:17,593 --> 01:44:19,801
- You wanna take a look?
- No. Uh, thanks.

1141
01:44:19,887 --> 01:44:22,425
- I... I can't stand rats.
- [laughs]

1142
01:44:22,514 --> 01:44:23,880
I understand.

1143
01:45:03,263 --> 01:45:06,097
[no audible dialogue]

1144
01:45:09,144 --> 01:45:10,260
[Usher] "Murder."

1145
01:45:14,525 --> 01:45:15,936
Let him talk.

1146
01:45:21,490 --> 01:45:25,279
[doorbell ringing]

1147
01:45:32,793 --> 01:45:35,035
- [detective] Surprised?
- [Usher] Not really.

1148
01:45:35,128 --> 01:45:38,872
Not really? [laughs]

1149
01:45:38,966 --> 01:45:41,834
False accusations
are like the wind.

1150
01:45:43,595 --> 01:45:48,135
- At least I'm lucky they sent you.
- Yeah. Well, we'll see how lucky you are.

1151
01:45:48,225 --> 01:45:51,184
You know, Rod, they mentioned your name
down at the precinct, and I said,

1152
01:45:51,270 --> 01:45:55,731
- "I know that guy. He's an artiste."
- [laughs]

1153
01:45:55,816 --> 01:45:58,058
Let's not stand on ceremony.
Have a seat.

1154
01:45:58,151 --> 01:46:02,646
Oh, we like standing.
But we prefer walking. Check it out.

1155
01:46:05,576 --> 01:46:07,192
[rustling]

1156
01:46:07,286 --> 01:46:11,246
[sighs] I haven't had breakfast yet,
and I've got a lot of errands to run.

1157
01:46:11,331 --> 01:46:13,618
Hmm. Well, we won't be long.

1158
01:46:15,586 --> 01:46:17,202
[clicking phone cradle]

1159
01:46:19,298 --> 01:46:20,960
- Phone's unplugged.
- Oh.

1160
01:46:22,634 --> 01:46:26,048
There have been a lot of kook
calls since the book came out.

1161
01:46:26,138 --> 01:46:28,300
- Amateur photographers.
- [sneezes]

1162
01:46:28,390 --> 01:46:31,258
- God bless you.
- Is there a cat in here?

1163
01:46:33,353 --> 01:46:37,347
- There was one, but now it's gone.
- And what happened to it?

1164
01:46:38,317 --> 01:46:40,934
Don't tell me you're here
to search for a lost cat.

1165
01:46:41,028 --> 01:46:44,396
[chuckles]
I asked you something.

1166
01:46:44,489 --> 01:46:49,029
It was here for a few days,
and then it disappeared!

1167
01:46:49,119 --> 01:46:53,284
Disappeared, huh? Look,
speaking of disappearance, uh, Rod,

1168
01:46:53,373 --> 01:46:54,830
what happened to your wife?

1169
01:46:56,960 --> 01:46:58,041
She's not my wife.

1170
01:46:59,463 --> 01:47:03,628
[detective] Oh, right, right.
What was her name? Uh, Annabel.

1171
01:47:04,343 --> 01:47:07,051
What do you mean "was"?
It's still her name.

1172
01:47:07,971 --> 01:47:10,054
Well, past tense.

1173
01:47:10,140 --> 01:47:11,551
It's a bad habit.

1174
01:47:12,225 --> 01:47:15,309
It seems whenever you and I meet,
there's always a body around.

1175
01:47:33,372 --> 01:47:36,035
Okay, tell us where she is,
we'll have breakfast delivered.

1176
01:47:36,124 --> 01:47:38,912
I don't know! If I knew,
I'd tell you.

1177
01:47:44,383 --> 01:47:45,749
She left me.

1178
01:47:47,761 --> 01:47:50,253
We spent a couple
of days up at a lake.

1179
01:47:50,347 --> 01:47:52,179
We couldn't patch things up.

1180
01:47:53,642 --> 01:47:57,602
- She has a sister who lives in...
- No, her sister hasn't heard from her.

1181
01:47:58,981 --> 01:48:00,768
No wonder.
They don't like each other.

1182
01:48:10,242 --> 01:48:11,983
[sneezes] Excuse me.

1183
01:48:12,077 --> 01:48:15,912
That cat of yours must have
left a lot of fur behind, huh?

1184
01:48:18,041 --> 01:48:20,454
Say, this is the cat,
isn't it, Rod?

1185
01:48:23,505 --> 01:48:28,341
You know, Rod, they say that you... you
tortured this cat to get these pictures.

1186
01:48:29,302 --> 01:48:30,964
Now you wouldn't do that,
would you?

1187
01:48:31,680 --> 01:48:33,296
Say it isn't so, Rod.

1188
01:48:34,099 --> 01:48:35,260
It isn't so.

1189
01:48:36,059 --> 01:48:37,059
Good.

1190
01:48:37,644 --> 01:48:40,933
My kid has a couple
of little kittens. Loves 'em.

1191
01:48:41,648 --> 01:48:44,140
- Plays with 'em all the time.
- [man] Great, Legrand!

1192
01:48:44,234 --> 01:48:46,087
Have Rod take care of 'em
when you go on vacation.

1193
01:48:46,111 --> 01:48:47,602
[chuckles]

1194
01:48:48,613 --> 01:48:51,105
[phone rings]

1195
01:48:52,492 --> 01:48:54,654
- Hello.
- [Joseph] <i>This is Joseph.</i>

1196
01:48:54,745 --> 01:48:56,407
<i>I called yesterday
from New York.</i>

1197
01:48:58,081 --> 01:48:59,684
[British accent]
You wish to speak with Mr. Usher.

1198
01:48:59,708 --> 01:49:02,121
Sorry, Mr. Usher is not at home.

1199
01:49:02,210 --> 01:49:03,326
[hangs up]

1200
01:49:03,879 --> 01:49:05,523
[normal voice] Pain in the ass
won't leave me alone.

1201
01:49:05,547 --> 01:49:07,254
- Ah.
- Wants some of my pictures.

1202
01:49:07,340 --> 01:49:08,660
I have to get an unlisted number.

1203
01:49:08,717 --> 01:49:13,678
Ah. So Annabel and the cat took off, huh?
Didn't say where they were going, though.

1204
01:49:13,764 --> 01:49:16,598
Cats don't talk.
But Annabel left a note.

1205
01:49:17,142 --> 01:49:18,633
It's around here somewhere.

1206
01:49:31,239 --> 01:49:33,697
[chuckles]
Real love letter.

1207
01:49:33,784 --> 01:49:37,152
Why'd you tell the neighbors
that she was going on an orchestra tour?

1208
01:49:37,245 --> 01:49:40,864
I don't have to tell
those busybodies my business.

1209
01:49:40,957 --> 01:49:44,667
True. You got any letters of hers?

1210
01:49:44,753 --> 01:49:47,245
- This is her picture, isn't it?
- Yes.

1211
01:49:47,339 --> 01:49:49,752
- Do you mind if we take it?
- No.

1212
01:49:55,889 --> 01:49:58,973
Oh, and you could give me
the book as a present, huh?

1213
01:50:00,143 --> 01:50:01,143
[Usher] Sure.

1214
01:50:02,604 --> 01:50:05,267
- Thanks, Rod.
- You almost coauthored it with me.

1215
01:50:07,317 --> 01:50:11,607
Oh, one more thing. Um, where'd you
and Annabel go on this vacation of yours?

1216
01:50:11,696 --> 01:50:14,404
To Lake Arthur. I have a dual house
on the shore there.

1217
01:50:14,491 --> 01:50:18,110
Uh-huh. Okay, Rod, thank you.
Let's go.

1218
01:50:27,629 --> 01:50:30,121
Gentlemen, I'm glad
your suspicions have been allayed.

1219
01:50:30,215 --> 01:50:32,081
I wish you a long and happy life.

1220
01:50:33,718 --> 01:50:38,088
And what did you expect to find
between these solidly put-together walls?

1221
01:50:46,273 --> 01:50:48,856
[knocks]

1222
01:50:48,942 --> 01:50:50,683
[Legrand]
Open up. It's me again.

1223
01:50:50,777 --> 01:50:53,064
[knocking]

1224
01:50:56,867 --> 01:50:58,233
You forgot to sign it.

1225
01:51:07,294 --> 01:51:08,330
Ah.

1226
01:51:13,175 --> 01:51:15,292
That's funny. It was working
a minute ago.

1227
01:51:20,348 --> 01:51:22,431
I'm sure you got a pen inside.

1228
01:51:34,571 --> 01:51:36,779
Hey, Rod, I liked
what you said before

1229
01:51:36,865 --> 01:51:39,107
about me almost coauthoring
the book with you.

1230
01:51:39,201 --> 01:51:40,658
Would you sign it like that?

1231
01:51:46,208 --> 01:51:47,324
Yeah.

1232
01:51:49,878 --> 01:51:52,291
[cat screeching]

1233
01:51:52,380 --> 01:51:53,621
Where's that coming from?

1234
01:52:03,350 --> 01:52:05,433
[cat screeching]

1235
01:52:28,583 --> 01:52:32,293
[clattering]

1236
01:52:32,379 --> 01:52:34,746
- [shouting] What the fuck are you doing?
- Hold it.

1237
01:52:35,507 --> 01:52:36,793
What do you got?

1238
01:52:37,300 --> 01:52:39,337
[clattering stops]

1239
01:52:43,223 --> 01:52:44,259
Boss.

1240
01:53:00,699 --> 01:53:03,737
- It's fresh.
- What'd you say, Rod?

1241
01:53:03,827 --> 01:53:07,446
What'd we think we were gonna find
behind these solidly built walls?

1242
01:53:07,539 --> 01:53:09,496
A little guessing game, huh, Rod?

1243
01:53:10,083 --> 01:53:13,702
- [man] What do you think? Break it down?
- [Legrand] Sure.

